NAME
  xfarcs - drawing a set of ellipsis

CALLING SEQUENCE
  []=xfarcs(arcs,[style])

PARAMETERS

  arcs : matrix of size (6,n) (ellipsis description)

  style
       : vector of size (1,n) giving the style to use ( set
       xset("dashes",...).

DESCRIPTION
  draws a set of ellipsis described by arcs. arcs= [ x,y,w,h,a1,a2 ;
  x,y,w,h,a1,a2 ;.....] ' : each ellipsis is defined by the 6 parameters
  (x,y,w,h,a1,a2) (see xarc)

  fill(i) gives the dash style which must be used to draw the ellipsis number
  i.

EXAMPLE
  plot2d(0,0,-1,"031",' ',[-1,-1,1,1])
  set_arcs=[ -1.0 0.0 0.5 // upper left x
              1.0 0.0 0.5 // upper left y
              0.5 0.5 0.5 // widths
              0.5 0.5 0.5 // height
              0.0 0.0 0.0 // angle 1
              360*64 360*64 360*64] // angle 2
  xfarcs(set_arcs,[0,1,2])

